com.stormpath.sdk.saml

Class SamlIdentityProviders

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.stormpath.sdk.saml.SamlIdentityProviders

  • public class SamlIdentityProviders
extends Object
    Static utility/helper methods for working with SamlIdentityProvider resources. Most methods are factory methods used for forming SamlIdentityProvider-specific fluent DSL queries. For example: 
     SamlIdentityProviders.where(SamlIdentityProviders.createdAt().eq("2016-01-01"))
     .withRegisteredSamlServiceProviders()
     .offsetBy(50)
     .limitTo(25));
    Since:
    1.3.0

      • criteria

        public static SamlIdentityProviderCriteria criteria()
        Returns a new SamlIdentityProviderCriteria instance to use to formulate a SamlIdentityProvider query.

        Note that it is usually more common to use the where method instead of this one as the where method usually lends to better readability. For example: 

         SamlIdentityProviders.criteria().add(SamlIdentityProviders.createdAt().eq("2016-01-01"))...
        versus: 
         SamlIdentityProviders.where(SamlIdentityProviders.createdAt().eq("2016-01-01"))...
        or when using static imports: 
         where(createdAt().eq("2016-01-01"))...
        While all three statements are equivalent, the second and third examples are shorter and probably more readable.
        Returns:
        a new SamlIdentityProviderCriteria instance to use to formulate a Phone query.

      • where

        public static SamlIdentityProviderCriteria where(Criterion criterion)
        Returns a new RegisteredSamlServiceProviderCriteria instance to use to formulate a RegisteredSamlServiceProvide query.

        Note that it is usually more common to use the where method instead of this one as the where method usually lends to better readability. For example: 

         RegisteredSamlServiceProviders.criteria().add(RegisteredSamlServiceProviders.createdAt().eq("2016-01-01"))...
        versus: 
         RegisteredSamlServiceProviders.where(RegisteredSamlServiceProviders.createdAt().eq("2016-01-01"))...
        or when using static imports: 
         where(createdAt().eq("2016-01-01"))...
        While all three statements are equivalent, the second and third examples are shorter and probably more readable.
        Returns:
        a new RegisteredSamlServiceProviderCriteria instance to use to formulate a Phone query.

      • createdAt

        public static DateExpressionFactory createdAt()
        Creates a new DateExpressionFactory instance reflecting the SamlIdentityProvider createdAt property, to be used to construct a createdAt Criterion when building an SamlIdentityProviderCriteria query. For example: 
         SamlIdentityProviders.where(SamlIdentityProviders.createdAt().matches("[,2014-04-05T12:00:00]");
        The above example invokes the returned factory's matches("[,2014-04-05T12:00:00]")) method. This produces a createdAt-specific Criterion which is added to the criteria query (via the where method). 
         For example, the following code is equivalent:
 
         SamlIdentityProviderCriteria criteria = SamlIdentityProviders.criteria();
 DateExpressionFactory createdAt = SamlIdentityProviders.createdAt();
 Criterion createdAtMatches = createdAt.matches("[,2014-04-05T12:00:00]");
 criteria.add(createdAtMatches);
        Returns:
        a new createdAt-specific DateExpressionFactory instance, to be used to construct a criterion when building an SamlIdentityProviderCriteria query.

      • modifiedAt

        public static DateExpressionFactory modifiedAt()
        Creates a new DateExpressionFactory instance reflecting the SamlIdentityProvider modifiedAt property, to be used to construct a modifiedAt Criterion when building an SamlIdentityProviderCriteria query. For example: 
         SamlIdentityProviders.where(SamlIdentityProviders.createdAt().matches("[,2014-04-05T12:00:00]");
        The above example invokes the returned factory's matches("[,2014-04-05T12:00:00]")) method. This produces a modifiedAt-specific Criterion which is added to the criteria query (via the where method). 
         For example, the following code is equivalent:
 
         SamlIdentityProviderCriteria criteria = SamlIdentityProviders.criteria();
 DateExpressionFactory modifiedAt = SamlIdentityProviders.modifiedAt();
 Criterion modifiedAtMatches = modifiedAt.matches("[,2014-04-05T12:00:00]");
 criteria.add(modifiedAtMatches);
        Returns:
        a new Auditable.getModifiedAt() modifiedAt}-specific DateExpressionFactory instance, to be used to construct a criterion when building an SamlIdentityProviderCriteria query.
